##Project overview
This project focuses on analysing customer churn behaviour using an interactive Power BI dashboard.
The objective was to understand why customers leave, identify risk patterns, and propose data-driven business solutions to reduce churn.

##Business overview
Identify factors influencing customer churn.
Analyse customer behaviour based on contract, tenure, and services.
Understand revenue impact caused by churn.
Suggest possible retention strategies using data insights.

##Tools used
Power BI | Data Cleaning | Data Modelling | Dashboard Design

##business insight
Month-to-month contracts showed higher churn risk compared to long-term contracts.
Customers with higher monthly charges showed stronger churn patterns.
Lack of services such as Tech Support and Online Security correlated with higher churn levels.
Tenure analysis revealed early-stage customers are more likely to leave.

